  <div class="policy-section" id="safeguarding">
    <h2>Safeguarding Policy</h2>
    <p>Steyning Town Community FC is committed to the safeguarding and protection of all children, young people and vulnerable adults involved in football at our club. The welfare of every player is our highest priority.</p>
    <p>Our club holds <strong>★★ England Football Accreditation</strong>, the highest community club standard in English football, which includes rigorous safeguarding requirements.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>All coaches and volunteers working with children hold a valid FA-enhanced DBS check</li>
      <li>All staff complete FA Safeguarding Children training</li>
      <li>We follow the FA's Safeguarding Policy and Procedures</li>
      <li>Any safeguarding concerns should be reported to our Club Welfare Officer immediately</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="policy-placeholder">The full Steyning Town Community FC Safeguarding Policy document is available on request. Please email <a href="mailto:steyningtownfc@gmail.com" style="color:var(--red)">steyningtownfc@gmail.com</a> to request a copy.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section" id="privacy">
    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>Steyning Town Community FC ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use and protect your personal information.</p>
    <p><strong>What information we collect:</strong> When you register with the club or contact us, we may collect your name, email address, phone number, date of birth (for age group verification) and emergency contact details.</p>
    <p><strong>How we use your information:</strong> We use your information to manage your club membership, contact you about training and fixtures, and comply with FA registration requirements. We do not sell your data to third parties.</p>
    <p><strong>How we store your information:</strong> Your information is stored securely and only accessible to club officials with a legitimate need. We retain membership data for the duration of your membership plus two years.</p>
    <p><strong>Your rights:</strong> You have the right to access, correct or request deletion of your personal data at any time. Email <a href="mailto:steyningtownfc@gmail.com">steyningtownfc@gmail.com</a> to exercise these rights.</p>
    <p><strong>Contact:</strong> For privacy enquiries contact the Club Secretary at <a href="mailto:steyningtownfc@gmail.com">steyningtownfc@gmail.com</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section" id="cookies">
    <h2>Cookie Policy</h2>
    <p>This website uses cookies to improve your experience. Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website.</p>
    <p><strong>Cookies we use:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong> — required for the website to function correctly. These cannot be disabled.</li>
      <li><strong>Preference cookies</strong> — remember your cookie consent choice so we don't ask you every visit.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not use advertising, tracking or analytics cookies. You can clear cookies at any time through your browser settings.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section" id="complaints">
    <h2>Complaints & Discipline</h2>
    <p>Steyning Town Community FC is affiliated to the Football Association and abides by the FA's Rules and Regulations. All members, players, coaches and spectators are expected to follow the FA's Respect programme and Code of Conduct.</p>
    <p>Any complaints about the conduct of club members or officials should be made in writing to the Club Secretary at <a href="mailto:steyningtownfc@gmail.com">steyningtownfc@gmail.com</a>. Complaints will be dealt with in accordance with FA guidelines.</p>
  </div>

